<inglise> Directive 95/46/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 24 October 1995 on the protection of individuals with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA PARLAMENDI JA N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 95/46/E&Uuml; &uuml;ksikisikute kaitse kohta isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisel ja selliste andmete vaba liikumise kohta 24. oktoober 1995 </eesti>
<inglise> THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA PARLAMENT JA EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 100a thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 100a, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure referred to in Article 189b of the Treaty (3), </inglise>
<eesti> toimides asutamislepingu artiklis 189b osutatud korras (3) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas the objectives of the Community, as laid down in the Treaty, as amended by the Treaty on European Union, include creating an ever closer union among the peoples of Europe, fostering closer relations between the States belonging to the Community, ensuring economic and social progress by common action to eliminate the barriers which divide Europe, encouraging the constant improvement of the living conditions of its peoples, preserving and strengthening peace and liberty and promoting democracy on the basis of the fundamental rights recognized in the constitution and laws of the Member States and in the European Convention for the Protection of Human Rights and Fundamental Freedoms; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) asutamislepingus, mida on muudetud Euroopa Liidu lepinguga, on &uuml;henduse eesm&auml;rkidena s&auml;testatud &uuml;ha tugevama liidu loomine Euroopa rahvaste vahel, &uuml;hendusse kuuluvate riikide vaheliste tihedate suhete edendamine, majandusliku ja sotsiaalse arengu tagamine Euroopat jagavate t&otilde;kete k&otilde;rvaldamiseks v&otilde;etavate &uuml;hismeetmete abil, rahvaste elutingimuste j&auml;tkuva parandamise soodustamine, rahu ja vabaduse s&auml;ilitamine ja tugevdamine ning demokraatia edendamine, l&auml;htudes liikmesriikide p&otilde;hiseadustes ja &otilde;igusaktides ning Euroopa inim&otilde;iguste ja p&otilde;hivabaduste kaitse konventsioonis tunnustatud p&otilde;hi&otilde;igustest; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas data-processing systems are designed to serve man; whereas they must, whatever the nationality or residence of natural persons, respect their fundamental rights and freedoms, notably the right to privacy, and contribute to economic and social progress, trade expansion and the well-being of individuals; (3) Whereas the establishment and functioning of an internal market in which, in accordance with Article 7a of the Treaty, the free movement of goods, persons, services and capital is ensured require not only that personal data should be able to flow freely from one Member State to another, but also that the fundamental rights of individuals should be safeguarded; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) andmet&ouml;&ouml;tluss&uuml;steemid on loodud selleks, et teenida inimkonda; selliseid s&uuml;steeme kasutades tuleb f&uuml;&uuml;siliste isikute kodakondsusele ja elukohale vaatamata austada nende p&otilde;hi&otilde;igusi ja -vabadusi, eelk&otilde;ige &otilde;igust eraelu puutumatusele, ning aidata kaasa majanduslikule ja sotsiaalsele arengule, kaubanduse laiendamisele ja &uuml;ksikisikute heaolule; 3) sellise siseturu rajamine ja toimimine, kus on vastavalt asutamislepingu artiklile 7a tagatud kaupade, isikute, teenuste ja kapitali vaba liikumine, ei eelda mitte ainult isikuandmete vaba liikumist &uuml;hest liikmesriigist teise, vaid ka &uuml;ksikisikute p&otilde;hi&otilde;iguste kaitset; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas increasingly frequent recourse is being had in the Community to the processing of personal data in the various spheres of economic and social activity; whereas the progress made in information technology is making the processing and exchange of such data considerably easier; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) &uuml;henduse majandus- ja &uuml;hiskondliku elu eri valdkondades kasutatakse &uuml;ha sagedamini isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemist; infotehnoloogia areng teeb selliste andmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise ja vahetamise m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rselt lihtsamaks; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas the economic and social integration resulting from the establishment and functioning of the internal market within the meaning of Article 7a of the Treaty will necessarily lead to a substantial increase in cross-border flows of personal data between all those involved in a private or public capacity in economic and social activity in the Member States; whereas the exchange of personal data between undertakings in different Member States is set to increase; whereas the national authorities in the various Member States are being called upon by virtue of Community law to collaborate and exchange personal data so as to be able to perform their duties or carry out tasks on behalf of an authority in another Member State within the context of the area without internal frontiers as constituted by the internal market; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) asutamislepingu artiklis 7a s&auml;testatud siseturu rajamisest ja toimimisest tuleneva majandusliku ja sotsiaalse integratsiooniga suureneb paratamatult kas era&otilde;iguslikus v&otilde;i avalik-&otilde;iguslikus sektoris liikmesriikide majanduslikus ja &uuml;hiskondlikus tegevuses osalevate inimeste isikuandmete liikumine &uuml;le piiride; eri liikmesriikides paiknevad ettev&otilde;tjad peaksid isikuandmeid vahetama ulatuslikumalt; &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse alusel on eri liikmesriikide siseriiklikke ametiasutusi kutsutud &uuml;les tegema koost&ouml;&ouml;d ja vahetama isikuandmeid, et oleks v&otilde;imalik t&auml;ita oma kohustusi v&otilde;i &uuml;lesandeid teise liikmesriigi ametiasutuste nimel siseturuna m&auml;&auml;ratletud piirideta alal; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas, furthermore, the increase in scientific and technical cooperation and the coordinated introduction of new telecommunications networks in the Community necessitate and facilitate cross-border flows of personal data; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) lisaks sellele on isikuandmete liikumine &uuml;le piiride vajalik ka seoses tihedama teadus- ja tehnikaalase koost&ouml;&ouml; ning uute telekommunikatsiooniv&otilde;rkude koosk&otilde;lastatud kasutuselev&otilde;tmisega &uuml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas the difference in levels of protection of the rights and freedoms of individuals, notably the right to privacy, with regard to the processing of personal data afforded in the Member States may prevent the transmission of such data from the territory of one Member State to that of another Member State; whereas this difference may therefore constitute an obstacle to the pursuit of a number of economic activities at Community level, distort competition and impede authorities in the discharge of their responsibilities under Community law; whereas this difference in levels of protection is due to the existence of a wide variety of national laws, regulations and administrative provisions; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) &uuml;ksikisikute &otilde;iguste ja vabaduste, eelk&otilde;ige eraelu puutumatuse &otilde;iguse kaitse tase seoses isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisega on liikmesriigiti erinev ja see v&otilde;ib takistada selliste andmete edastamist &uuml;hest liikmesriigist teise; seega v&otilde;ivad nimetatud erinevused saada takistuseks paljudele &uuml;henduse tasandi majandustegevustele, moonutada konkurentsi ja takistada ametiasutusi nende &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusest tulenevate kohustuste t&auml;itmisel; k&otilde;nealused erinevused kaitse tasemes tulenevad kehtivate siseriiklike &otilde;igusnormide mitmekesisusest; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas, in order to remove the obstacles to flows of personal data, the level of protection of the rights and freedoms of individuals with regard to the processing of such data must be equivalent in all Member States; whereas this objective is vital to the internal market but cannot be achieved by the Member States alone, especially in view of the scale of the divergences which currently exist between the relevant laws in the Member States and the need to coordinate the laws of the Member States so as to ensure that the cross-border flow of personal data is regulated in a consistent manner that is in keeping with the objective of the internal market as provided for in Article 7a of the Treaty; whereas Community action to approximate those laws is therefore needed; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) takistuste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks isikuandmete liikumisel peab selliste andmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisega seotud &uuml;ksikisikute &otilde;iguste ja vabaduste kaitse olema k&otilde;igis liikmesriikides samal tasemel; nimetatud eesm&auml;rk on siseturu seisukohast &auml;&auml;rmiselt oluline, kuid liikmesriigid ei saa seda saavutada &uuml;ksi, silmas pidades liikmesriikide asjaomaste &otilde;igusaktide praegusi ulatuslikke erinevusi ja vajadust koosk&otilde;lastada liikmesriikide &otilde;igusakte tagamaks, et isikuandmete piiri&uuml;lest liikumist reguleeritaks j&auml;rjepidevalt ja viisil, mis on koosk&otilde;las asutamislepingu artiklis 7a s&auml;testatud siseturu eesm&auml;rgiga; seet&otilde;ttu on k&otilde;nealuste &otilde;igusaktide &uuml;htlustamiseks vaja &uuml;henduse meetmeid; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Whereas, given the equivalent protection resulting from the approximation of national laws, the Member States will no longer be able to inhibit the free movement between them of personal data on grounds relating to protection of the rights and freedoms of individuals, and in particular the right to privacy; whereas Member States will be left a margin for manoeuvre, which may, in the context of implementation of the Directive, also be exercised by the business and social partners; whereas Member States will therefore be able to specify in their national law the general conditions governing the lawfulness of data processing; whereas in doing so the Member States shall strive to improve the protection currently provided by their legislation; whereas, within the limits of this margin for manoeuvre and in accordance with Community law, disparities could arise in the implementation of the Directive, and this could have an effect on the movement of data within a Member State as well as within the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) kuna siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide &uuml;htlustamisega saavutatakse samav&auml;&auml;rne kaitstuse tase, ei saa liikmesriigid enam takistada isikuandmete vaba liikumist &uuml;hest liikmesriigist teise p&otilde;hjustel, mis on seotud &uuml;ksikisikute &otilde;iguste ja vabaduste, eelk&otilde;ige eraelu puutumatuse &otilde;iguse kaitsmisega; liikmesriikidele j&auml;etakse tegutsemisruum, mida v&otilde;ivad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi rakendamisel kasutada ka &auml;ripartnerid ja t&ouml;&ouml;suhte pooled; seega saavad liikmesriigid oma siseriiklikes &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testada andmet&ouml;&ouml;tluse seaduslikkust reguleerivad &uuml;ldised tingimused; selliselt toimides p&uuml;&uuml;avad liikmesriigid t&auml;iustada oma praeguste &otilde;igusaktidega s&auml;testatud kaitset; nimetatud tegutsemisruumi piires ja koosk&otilde;las &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusega v&otilde;ivad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi rakendamisel tekkida lahknevused ja see v&otilde;ib m&otilde;jutada andmete liikumist liikmesriigi piires ja &uuml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) Whereas the object of the national laws on the processing of personal data is to protect fundamental rights and freedoms, notably the right to privacy, which is recognized both in Article 8 of the European Convention for the Protection of Human Rights and Fundamental Freedoms and in the general principles of Community law; whereas, for that reason, the approximation of those laws must not result in any lessening of the protection they afford but must, on the contrary, seek to ensure a high level of protection in the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> 10) isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemist k&auml;sitlevate &otilde;igusaktide eesm&auml;rk on kaitsta Euroopa inim&otilde;iguste ja p&otilde;hivabaduste kaitse konventsiooni artiklis 8 ja &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse &uuml;ldistes p&otilde;him&otilde;tetes tunnustatud p&otilde;hi&otilde;igusi ja -vabadusi, eelk&otilde;ige &otilde;igust eraelu puutumatusele; nimetatud p&otilde;hjusel ei tohi k&otilde;nealuste &otilde;igusaktide &uuml;htlustamise tagaj&auml;rjel nendega pakutav kaitse v&auml;heneda, vaid vastupidi - &uuml;henduses tagatava kaitstuse tase peab olema k&otilde;rgem; </eesti>
<inglise> (11) Whereas the principles of the protection of the rights and freedoms of individuals, notably the right to privacy, which are contained in this Directive, give substance to and amplify those contained in the Council of Europe Convention of 28 January 1981 for the Protection of Individuals with regard to Automatic Processing of Personal Data; </inglise>
<eesti> 11) k&auml;esolevas direktiivis sisalduvad &uuml;ksikisikute &otilde;iguste ja vabaduste, eriti eraelu puutumatuse &otilde;iguse kaitsmise p&otilde;him&otilde;tted t&auml;psustavad ja v&otilde;imendavad p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid, mida sisaldab Euroopa N&otilde;ukogu 28. jaanuari 1981. aasta konventsioon isikuandmete automatiseeritud t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisel isiku kaitse kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (12) Whereas the protection principles must apply to all processing of personal data by any person whose activities are governed by Community law; whereas there should be excluded the processing of data carried out by a natural person in the exercise of activities which are exclusively personal or domestic, such as correspondence and the holding of records of addresses; </inglise>
<eesti> 12) kaitsmise p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid tuleb kohaldada igasuguse isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise suhtes, kui sellega tegeleva isiku toimingud kuuluvad &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse reguleerimisalasse; erand tuleks teha, kui andmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisega tegelevad f&uuml;&uuml;silised isikud &uuml;ksnes isiklikel v&otilde;i kodustel eesm&auml;rkidel, n&auml;iteks kirjavahetus ja aadresside loetelu; </eesti>
<inglise> (13) Whereas the acitivities referred to in Titles V and VI of the Treaty on European Union regarding public safety, defence, State security or the acitivities of the State in the area of criminal laws fall outside the scope of Community law, without prejudice to the obligations incumbent upon Member States under Article 56 (2), Article 57 or Article 100a of the Treaty establishing the European Community; whereas the processing of personal data that is necessary to safeguard the economic well-being of the State does not fall within the scope of this Directive where such processing relates to State security matters; </inglise>
<eesti> 13) Euroopa Liidu lepingu V j VI jaotises osutatud avaliku korra, riigikaitse, riigi julgeoleku ja riigi toimingutega kriminaal&otilde;iguse valdkonnas seotud tegevus ei kuulu &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse reguleerimisalasse, ilma et see piiraks Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingu artikli 56 l&otilde;ikest 2, artiklist 57 v&otilde;i artiklist 100a tulenevaid liikmesriikide kohustusi; riigi majandusliku heaolu tagamiseks vajalik isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine ei kuulu k&auml;esoleva direktiivi reguleerimisalasse, kui selline t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine on seotud riikliku julgeoleku k&uuml;simustega; </eesti>
<inglise> (14) Whereas, given the importance of the developments under way, in the framework of the information society, of the techniques used to capture, transmit, manipulate, record, store or communicate sound and image data relating to natural persons, this Directive should be applicable to processing involving such data; </inglise>
<eesti> 14) v&otilde;ttes arvesse info&uuml;hiskonnas praegu toimuvat f&uuml;&uuml;siliste isikutega seotud heli- ja pildiandmete kogumise, edastamise, t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise, salvestamise, talletamise ja vahendamise tehnoloogia arengut ja sellise arengu olulisust, peaks k&auml;esolev direktiiv olema kohaldatav ka selliste andmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise> (15) Whereas the processing of such data is covered by this Directive only if it is automated or if the data processed are contained or are intended to be contained in a filing system structured according to specific criteria relating to individuals, so as to permit easy access to the personal data in question; </inglise>
<eesti> 15) selliste andmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine kuulub k&auml;esoleva direktiivi reguleerimisalasse ainult siis, kui tegemist on automatiseeritud t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisega v&otilde;i kui t&ouml;&ouml;deldavad andmed sisalduvad &uuml;ksikisikutega seotud teatavate kriteeriumide p&otilde;hjal korrastatud kataloogis v&otilde;i kui nad hiljem kantakse sellisesse kataloogi, et v&otilde;imaldada lihtsat juurdep&auml;&auml;su k&otilde;nealustele isikuandmetele; </eesti>
<inglise> (16) Whereas the processing of sound and image data, such as in cases of video surveillance, does not come within the scope of this Directive if it is carried out for the purposes of public security, defence, national security or in the course of State activities relating to the area of criminal law or of other activities which do not come within the scope of Community law; </inglise>
<eesti> 16) heli- ja pildimaterjali sisaldavate andmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine, n&auml;iteks videovalve puhul, ei kuulu k&auml;esoleva direktiivi reguleerimisalasse, kui see on seotud avaliku korra, riigikaitse, riigi julgeoleku v&otilde;i riigi toimingutega kriminaal&otilde;iguse valdkonnas v&otilde;i muu tegevusega, mis ei kuulu &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse reguleerimisalasse; </eesti>
<inglise> (17) Whereas, as far as the processing of sound and image data carried out for purposes of journalism or the purposes of literary or artistic expression is concerned, in particular in the audiovisual field, the principles of the Directive are to apply in a restricted manner according to the provisions laid down in Article 9; </inglise>
<eesti> 17) kui tegemist on heli- ja pildimaterjali sisaldavate andmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisega ajakirjanduse jaoks v&otilde;i kirjandusliku v&otilde;i kunstilise enesev&auml;ljenduse huvides, eelk&otilde;ige audiovisuaalsektoris, kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva direktiivi p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid piiratult vastavalt artikli 9 s&auml;tetele; </eesti>
<inglise> (18) Whereas, in order to ensure that individuals are not deprived of the protection to which they are entitled under this Directive, any processing of personal data in the Community must be carried out in accordance with the law of one of the Member States; whereas, in this connection, processing carried out under the responsibility of a controller who is established in a Member State should be governed by the law of that State; </inglise>
<eesti> 18) tagamaks, et &uuml;ksikisikud ei j&auml;&auml; ilma kaitsest, millele neil on k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaselt &otilde;igus, peab igasugune isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine &uuml;henduses toimuma &uuml;he liikmesriigi &otilde;iguse kohaselt; seoses sellega peaks &uuml;hes liikmesriigis registreeritud vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja andmeid t&ouml;&ouml;tlema vastavalt k&otilde;nealuse riigi &otilde;igusele; </eesti>
<inglise> (19) Whereas establishment on the territory of a Member State implies the effective and real exercise of activity through stable arrangements; whereas the legal form of such an establishment, whether simply branch or a subsidiary with a legal personality, is not the determining factor in this respect; whereas, when a single controller is established on the territory of several Member States, particularly by means of subsidiaries, he must ensure, in order to avoid any circumvention of national rules, that each of the establishments fulfils the obligations imposed by the national law applicable to its activities; </inglise>
<eesti> 19) registreerimine liikmesriigi territooriumil eeldab tegelikku ja tulemuslikku tegutsemist ning stabiilset asukohta; selles suhtes ei ole m&auml;&auml;ravaks asutatud &uuml;ksuse &otilde;iguslik vorm, tegemist v&otilde;ib olla lihtsalt filiaali v&otilde;i juriidilisest isikust t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjaga; kui &uuml;ks vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja on registreeritud mitme liikmesriigi territooriumil, eelk&otilde;ige t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjate kaudu, peab ta tagama, et k&otilde;ik ettev&otilde;tjad t&auml;idavad oma tegevuse suhtes kohaldatavast siseriiklikust &otilde;igusest tulenevaid kohustusi, et v&auml;ltida v&otilde;imalikku siseriiklikest eeskirjadest k&otilde;rvalehoidmist; </eesti>
<inglise> (20) Whereas the fact that the processing of data is carried out by a person established in a third country must not stand in the way of the protection of individuals provided for in this Directive; whereas in these cases, the processing should be governed by the law of the Member State in which the means used are located, and there should be guarantees to ensure that the rights and obligations provided for in this Directive are respected in practice; </inglise>
<eesti> 20) asjaolu, et andmeid t&ouml;&ouml;tleb kolmandas riigis registreeritud isik, ei tohi takistada &uuml;ksikisikute kaitsmist k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaselt; sellisel juhul peaks t&ouml;&ouml;tlemist reguleerima selle liikmesriigi &otilde;igus, kus asuvad kasutatavad vahendid, ning tagada tuleks see, et k&auml;esolevas direktiivis s&auml;testatud &otilde;igusi ja kohustusi tegelikult j&auml;rgitakse; </eesti>
<inglise> (21) Whereas this Directive is without prejudice to the rules of territoriality applicable in criminal matters; </inglise>
<eesti> 21) k&auml;esolev direktiiv ei piira kriminaalasjades kohaldatavaid territoriaalsuse p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid; </eesti>
<inglise> (22) Whereas Member States shall more precisely define in the laws they enact or when bringing into force the measures taken under this Directive the general circumstances in which processing is lawful; whereas in particular Article 5, in conjunction with Articles 7 and 8, allows Member States, independently of general rules, to provide for special processing conditions for specific sectors and for the various categories of data covered by Article 8; </inglise>
<eesti> 22) liikmesriigid m&auml;&auml;ravad enda j&otilde;ustatavates &otilde;igusaktides v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaseid meetmeid ellu viies t&auml;psemalt kindlaks &uuml;ldised asjaolud, mille korral on andmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine seaduslik; eelk&otilde;ige artikkel 5 koostoimes artiklitega 7 ja 8 v&otilde;imaldab liikmesriikidel &uuml;ldeeskirjadest olenemata s&auml;testada t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise eritingimused konkreetsete sektorite ja artikliga 8 etten&auml;htud eri andmeliikide jaoks; </eesti>
<inglise> (23) Whereas Member States are empowered to ensure the implementation of the protection of individuals both by means of a general law on the protection of individuals as regards the processing of personal data and by sectorial laws such as those relating, for example, to statistical institutes; </inglise>
<eesti> 23) liikmesriigid on volitatud tagama &uuml;ksikisikute kaitset nii &uuml;ldkohaldatavate &otilde;igusaktidega &uuml;ksikisikute kaitse kohta isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisel kui ka teatavates sektorites kohaldatavate &otilde;igusaktidega, n&auml;iteks nendega, mis k&auml;sitlevad statistikaasutusi; </eesti>
<inglise> (24) Whereas the legislation concerning the protection of legal persons with regard to the processing data which concerns them is not affected by this Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> 24) k&auml;esolev direktiiv ei m&otilde;juta &otilde;igusakte, mis k&auml;sitlevad juriidiliste isikute kaitset nende kohta k&auml;ivate andmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisel; </eesti>
<inglise> (25) Whereas the principles of protection must be reflected, on the one hand, in the obligations imposed on persons, public authorities, enterprises, agencies or other bodies responsible for processing, in particular regarding data quality, technical security, notification to the supervisory authority, and the circumstances under which processing can be carried out, and, on the other hand, in the right conferred on individuals, the data on whom are the subject of processing, to be informed that processing is taking place, to consult the data, to request corrections and even to object to processing in certain circumstances; </inglise>
