<inglise> HAVE ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> CHAPTER I GENERAL PROVISIONS </inglise>
<eesti> I PEAT&Uuml;KK &Uuml;LDS&Auml;TTED </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Object of the Directive </inglise>
<eesti> Direktiivi eesm&auml;rk </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> In accordance with this Directive, Member States shall protect the fundamental rights and freedoms of natural persons, and in particular their right to privacy with respect to the processing of personal data. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt k&auml;esolevale direktiivile kaitsevad liikmesriigid isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisel f&uuml;&uuml;siliste isikute p&otilde;hi&otilde;igusi ja -vabadusi ning eelk&otilde;ige nende &otilde;igust eraelu puutumatusele. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall neither restrict nor prohibit the free flow of personal data between Member States for reasons connected with the protection afforded under paragraph 1. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid ei piira ega keela isikuandmete vaba liikumist liikmesriikide vahel p&otilde;hjustel, mis on seotud l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud kaitsega. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Definitions </inglise>
<eesti> M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) 'personal data' shall mean any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person ('data subject'); an identifiable person is one who can be identified, directly or indirectly, in particular by reference to an identification number or to one or more factors specific to his physical, physiological, mental, economic, cultural or social identity; </inglise>
<eesti> a) isikuandmed - igasugune teave tuvastatud v&otilde;i tuvastatava f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku (edaspidi "andmesubjekt") kohta. Tuvastatav isik on isik, keda saab otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt tuvastada, eelk&otilde;ige isikukoodi p&otilde;hjal v&otilde;i &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitme tema f&uuml;&uuml;silisele, f&uuml;sioloogilisele, vaimsele, majanduslikule, kultuurilisele v&otilde;i sotsiaalsele identsusele omase joone p&otilde;hjal. </eesti>
<inglise> (b) 'processing of personal data' ('processing') shall mean any operation or set of operations which is performed upon personal data, whether or not by automatic means, such as collection, recording, organization, storage, adaptation or alteration, retrieval, consultation, use, disclosure by transmission, dissemination or otherwise making available, alignment or combination, blocking, erasure or destruction; </inglise>
<eesti> b) isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine (edaspidi "t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine") - iga isikuandmetega tehtav toiming v&otilde;i toimingute kogum, olenemata sellest, kas see on automatiseeritud v&otilde;i mitte, n&auml;iteks kogumine, salvestamine, korrastamine, s&auml;ilitamine, kohandamine v&otilde;i muutmine, v&auml;ljav&otilde;tete tegemine, p&auml;ringu teostamine, kasutamine, &uuml;leandmine, levitamine v&otilde;i muul moel avaldamine, &uuml;hitamine v&otilde;i &uuml;hendamine, sulgemine, kustutamine v&otilde;i h&auml;vitamine. </eesti>
<inglise> (c) 'personal data filing system' ('filing system') shall mean any structured set of personal data which are accessible according to specific criteria, whether centralized, decentralized or dispersed on a functional or geographical basis; </inglise>
<eesti> c) isikuandmete kataloog (edaspidi "kataloog") - k&otilde;ik isikuandmete korrastatud kogumid, millest v&otilde;ib andmeid saada teatavate kriteeriumide p&otilde;hjal, olenemata sellest, kas k&otilde;nealune andmete kogum on tsentraliseeritud, detsentraliseeritud v&otilde;i funktsionaalsetel v&otilde;i geograafilistel p&otilde;him&otilde;tetel hajutatud; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) 'controller' shall mean the natural or legal person, public authority, agency or any other body which alone or jointly with others determines the purposes and means of the processing of personal data; where the purposes and means of processing are determined by national or Community laws or regulations, the controller or the specific criteria for his nomination may be designated by national or Community law; </inglise>
<eesti> d) vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja - f&uuml;&uuml;siline v&otilde;i juriidiline isik, riigiasutus, esindused v&otilde;i m&otilde;ni muu organ, kes m&auml;&auml;rab &uuml;ksi v&otilde;i koos teistega kindlaks isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise eesm&auml;rgid ja vahendid; kui t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise eesm&auml;rgid ja vahendid on kindlaks m&auml;&auml;ratud siseriiklike v&otilde;i &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusnormidega, v&otilde;ib vastutava t&ouml;&ouml;tleja v&otilde;i tema ametissem&auml;&auml;ramise s&auml;testada siseriiklikus v&otilde;i &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguses; </eesti>
<inglise> (e) 'processor' shall mean a natural or legal person, public authority, agency or any other body which processes personal data on behalf of the controller; </inglise>
<eesti> e) volitatud t&ouml;&ouml;tleja - f&uuml;&uuml;siline v&otilde;i juriidiline isik, riigiasutus, esindused v&otilde;i m&otilde;ni muu organ, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tleb isikuandmeid vastutava t&ouml;&ouml;tleja nimel; </eesti>
<inglise> (f) 'third party' shall mean any natural or legal person, public authority, agency or any other body other than the data subject, the controller, the processor and the persons who, under the direct authority of the controller or the processor, are authorized to process the data; </inglise>
<eesti> f) kolmas isik - k&otilde;ik f&uuml;&uuml;silised v&otilde;i juriidilised isikud, riigiasutused, esindused v&otilde;i muud organid, v&auml;lja arvatud andmesubjekt, vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja, volitatud t&ouml;&ouml;tleja ja isikud, kes v&otilde;ivad andmeid t&ouml;&ouml;delda vastutava t&ouml;&ouml;tleja v&otilde;i volitatud t&ouml;&ouml;tleja otseses alluvuses; </eesti>
<inglise> (g) 'recipient' shall mean a natural or legal person, public authority, agency or any other body to whom data are disclosed, whether a third party or not; however, authorities which may receive data in the framework of a particular inquiry shall not be regarded as recipients; </inglise>
<eesti> g) vastuv&otilde;tja - f&uuml;&uuml;siline v&otilde;i juriidiline isik, riigiasutus, esindus v&otilde;i m&otilde;ni muu organ, kellele andmed avaldatakse, olenemata sellest, kas tegemist on kolmanda isikuga v&otilde;i mitte; vastuv&otilde;tjateks ei peeta siiski ametiasutusi, kes v&otilde;ivad andmeid saada seoses konkreetse j&auml;relep&auml;rimisega; </eesti>
<inglise> (h) 'the data subject's consent' shall mean any freely given specific and informed indication of his wishes by which the data subject signifies his agreement to personal data relating to him being processed. </inglise>
<eesti> h) andmesubjekti n&otilde;usolek - iga vabatahtlik, konkreetne ja teadlik tahteavaldus, millega andmesubjekt annab n&otilde;usoleku t&ouml;&ouml;delda tema kohta k&auml;ivaid andmeid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Scope </inglise>
<eesti> Reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive shall apply to the processing of personal data wholly or partly by automatic means, and to the processing otherwise than by automatic means of personal data which form part of a filing system or are intended to form part of a filing system. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat direktiivi kohaldatakse isikuandmete t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i osaliselt automatiseeritud t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise suhtes ja isikuandmete automatiseerimata t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise suhtes, kui k&otilde;nealused isikuandmed kuuluvad kataloogi v&otilde;i kui nad kavatsetakse hiljem sellesse kanda. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive shall not apply to the processing of personal data: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat direktiivi ei kohaldata isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise suhtes: </eesti>
<inglise> - in the course of an activity which falls outside the scope of Community law, such as those provided for by Titles V and VI of the Treaty on European Union and in any case to processing operations concerning public security, defence, State security (including the economic well-being of the State when the processing operation relates to State security matters) and the activities of the State in areas of criminal law, </inglise>
<eesti> - kui see toimub sellise tegevuse k&auml;igus, mis j&auml;&auml;b v&auml;ljapoole &uuml;henduse &otilde;igust, nagu n&auml;iteks Euroopa Liidu lepingu V j VI jaotises osutatud tegevused, ja igal juhul sellise t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise suhtes, mis on seotud avaliku korra, riigikaitse, riigi julgeoleku (sealhulgas riigi majanduslik heaolu, kui t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine on seotud riigi julgeoleku k&uuml;simustega) ja riigi toimingutega kriminaal&otilde;iguse valdkonnas, </eesti>
<inglise> - by a natural person in the course of a purely personal or household activity. </inglise>
<eesti> - kui seda teeb f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik isiklikel v&otilde;i kodustel eesm&auml;rkidel. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> National law applicable </inglise>
<eesti> Kohaldatav siseriiklik &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Each Member State shall apply the national provisions it adopts pursuant to this Directive to the processing of personal data where: </inglise>
<eesti> Iga liikmesriik kohaldab isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise suhtes k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaselt vastuv&otilde;etud siseriiklikke &otilde;igusnorme, kui: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the processing is carried out in the context of the activities of an establishment of the controller on the territory of the Member State; when the same controller is established on the territory of several Member States, he must take the necessary measures to ensure that each of these establishments complies with the obligations laid down by the national law applicable; </inglise>
<eesti> a) t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine toimub liikmesriigi territooriumil paikneva vastutava t&ouml;&ouml;tleja asutuse tegevuse raames; kui sama vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja on registreeritud mitme liikmesriigi territooriumil, peab ta v&otilde;tma vajalikke meetmeid tagamaks, et k&otilde;ik k&otilde;nealused asutused j&auml;rgivad kohaldatavates siseriiklikes &otilde;igusnormides s&auml;testatud kohustusi; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the controller is not established on the Member State's territory, but in a place where its national law applies by virtue of international public law; </inglise>
<eesti> b) vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja ei ole registreeritud mitte liikmesriigi territooriumil, vaid kohas, kus asjaomase liikmesriigi &otilde;igusnorme kohaldatakse rahvusvahelise avaliku &otilde;iguse kohaselt; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) the controller is not established on Community territory and, for purposes of processing personal data makes use of equipment, automated or otherwise, situated on the territory of the said Member State, unless such equipment is used only for purposes of transit through the territory of the Community. </inglise>
<eesti> c) vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja ei ole registreeritud &uuml;henduse territooriumil, kuid kasutab isikuandmete automatiseeritud v&otilde;i automatiseerimata t&ouml;&ouml;tlemiseks vahendeid, mis paiknevad k&otilde;nealuse liikmesriigi territooriumil, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui selliseid vahendeid kasutatakse ainult andmete edastamiseks &uuml;henduse territooriumi kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> In the circumstances referred to in paragraph 1 (c), the controller must designate a representative established in the territory of that Member State, without prejudice to legal actions which could be initiated against the controller himself. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ike 1 punktis c osutatud asjaoludel peab vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja m&auml;&auml;rama ametisse k&otilde;nealuse liikmesriigi territooriumil asuva esindaja, kuid see ei piira &otilde;iguslikke meetmeid, mida v&otilde;idakse v&otilde;tta vastutava t&ouml;&ouml;tleja enda suhtes. II PEAT&Uuml;KK </eesti>
<inglise> CHAPTER II GENERAL RULES ON THE LAWFULNESS OF THE PROCESSING OF PERSONAL DATA </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;LDISED EESKIRJAD ISIKUANDMETE T&Ouml;&Ouml;TLEMISE SEADUSLIKKUSE KOHTA </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall, within the limits of the provisions of this Chapter, determine more precisely the conditions under which the processing of personal data is lawful. </inglise>
<eesti> Kuiv&otilde;rd see on lubatud k&auml;esoleva peat&uuml;ki s&auml;tetega, m&auml;&auml;ravad liikmesriigid t&auml;psemalt kindlaks tingimused, mille puhul isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine on seaduslik. </eesti>
<inglise> SECTION I </inglise>
<eesti> I JAGU </eesti>
<inglise> PRINCIPLES RELATING TO DATA QUALITY </inglise>
<eesti> P&Otilde;HIM&Otilde;TTED ANDMETE KVALITEEDI KOHTA </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall provide that personal data must be: </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid s&auml;testavad selle, et </eesti>
<inglise> (a) processed fairly and lawfully; </inglise>
<eesti> a) isikuandmeid t&ouml;&ouml;deldakse &otilde;iglaselt ja seaduslikult; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) collected for specified, explicit and legitimate purposes and not further processed in a way incompatible with those purposes. </inglise>
<eesti> b) isikuandmeid kogutakse t&auml;pselt ja selgelt kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud ning &otilde;igusp&auml;rastel eesm&auml;rkidel ega t&ouml;&ouml;delda hiljem viisil, mis on vastuolus k&otilde;nealuste eesm&auml;rkidega. </eesti>
<inglise> Further processing of data for historical, statistical or scientific purposes shall not be considered as incompatible provided that Member States provide appropriate safeguards; </inglise>
<eesti> T&auml;iendavat t&ouml;&ouml;tlemist ajaloo, statistika v&otilde;i teadusega seotud eesm&auml;rkidel ei peeta vastuolus olevaks tingimusel, et liikmesriigid kannavad hoolt vajalike tagatiste eest; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) adequate, relevant and not excessive in relation to the purposes for which they are collected and/or further processed; </inglise>
<eesti> c) isikuandmed on piisavad, asjakohased ega &uuml;leta selle otstarbe piire, mille tarvis neid kogutakse ja/v&otilde;i hiljem t&ouml;&ouml;deldakse; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) accurate and, where necessary, kept up to date; every reasonable step must be taken to ensure that data which are inaccurate or incomplete, having regard to the purposes for which they were collected or for which they are further processed, are erased or rectified; </inglise>
<eesti> d) andmed on t&auml;psed ja vajaduse korral ajakohastatud; v&otilde;etakse k&otilde;ik m&otilde;istlikud meetmed, et kustutada v&otilde;i parandada andmete kogumise v&otilde;i hilisema t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise eesm&auml;rgi seisukohast eba&otilde;iged v&otilde;i mittet&auml;ielikud andmed </eesti>
<inglise> (e) kept in a form which permits identification of data subjects for no longer than is necessary for the purposes for which the data were collected or for which they are further processed. </inglise>
<eesti> e) isikuandmeid s&auml;ilitatakse kujul, mis v&otilde;imaldab andmesubjekte tuvastada ainult seni, kuni see on vajalik seoses andmete kogumise v&otilde;i hilisema t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise eesm&auml;rkidega. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall lay down appropriate safeguards for personal data stored for longer periods for historical, statistical or scientific use. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid kehtestavad vajalikud tagatised nende isikuandmete jaoks, mida s&auml;ilitatakse pikema aja jooksul, et neid kasutada seoses ajaloo, statistika v&otilde;i teadusega. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall be for the controller to ensure that paragraph 1 is complied with. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ike 1 j&auml;rgimise tagab vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja. </eesti>
<inglise> SECTION II </inglise>
<eesti> II JAGU </eesti>
<inglise> CRITERIA FOR MAKING DATA PROCESSING LEGITIMATE </inglise>
<eesti> ANDMET&Ouml;&Ouml;TLUSE SEADUSLIKKUSE KRITEERIUMID </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall provide that personal data may be processed only if: </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid s&auml;testavad, et isikuandmeid v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;delda ainult juhul, kui: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the data subject has unambiguously given his consent; or </inglise>
<eesti> a) andmesubjekt on selleks andnud oma &uuml;hem&otilde;ttelise n&otilde;usoleku v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> (b) processing is necessary for the performance of a contract to which the data subject is party or in order to take steps at the request of the data subject prior to entering into a contract; or </inglise>
<eesti> b) t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine on vajalik sellise lepingu t&auml;itmiseks, mille osapool andmesubjekt on, v&otilde;i lepingu s&otilde;lmimisele eelnevate meetmete v&otilde;tmiseks vastavalt andmesubjekti taotlusele v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> (c) processing is necessary for compliance with a legal obligation to which the controller is subject; or </inglise>
<eesti> c) t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine on vajalik vastutava t&ouml;&ouml;tleja seadusj&auml;rgse kohustuse t&auml;itmiseks v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> (d) processing is necessary in order to protect the vital interests of the data subject; or </inglise>
<eesti> d) t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine on vajalik andmesubjekti eluliste huvide kaitsmiseks v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> (e) processing is necessary for the performance of a task carried out in the public interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in the controller or in a third party to whom the data are disclosed; or </inglise>
<eesti> e) t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine on vajalik &uuml;ldiste huvidega seotud &uuml;lesande t&auml;itmiseks v&otilde;i sellise avaliku v&otilde;imu teostamiseks, mis on tehtud &uuml;lesandeks volitatud t&ouml;&ouml;tlejale v&otilde;i andmeid saavale kolmandale isikule, v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> (f) processing is necessary for the purposes of the legitimate interests pursued by the controller or by the third party or parties to whom the data are disclosed, except where such interests are overridden by the interests for fundamental rights and freedoms of the data subject which require protection under Article 1 (1). </inglise>
<eesti> f) t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine on vajalik vastutava t&ouml;&ouml;tleja v&otilde;i andmeid saava kolmanda isiku v&otilde;i kolmandate isikute &otilde;igustatud huvide elluviimiseks, kui selliseid huve ei kaalu &uuml;les artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 1 kohaselt kaitstavate andmesubjekti p&otilde;hi&otilde;iguste ja -vabadustega seotud huvid. </eesti>
<inglise> SECTION III </inglise>
<eesti> III JAGU </eesti>
<inglise> SPECIAL CATEGORIES OF PROCESSING </inglise>
<eesti> T&Ouml;&Ouml;TLEMISE ERI KATEGOORIAD </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> The processing of special categories of data </inglise>
<eesti> Andmete eriliikide t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall prohibit the processing of personal data revealing racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious or philosophical beliefs, trade-union membership, and the processing of data concerning health or sex life. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid keelavad t&ouml;&ouml;delda selliseid isikuandmeid, mis paljastavad rassilise v&otilde;i etnilise p&auml;ritolu, poliitilised vaated, usulised v&otilde;i filosoofilised veendumused, ameti&uuml;hingusse kuulumise, ning tervislikku seisundit v&otilde;i seksuaalelu k&auml;sitlevate andmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Paragraph 1 shall not apply where: </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;iget 1 ei kohaldata, kui: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the data subject has given his explicit consent to the processing of those data, except where the laws of the Member State provide that the prohibition referred to in paragraph 1 may not be lifted by the data subject's giving his consent; or </inglise>
<eesti> a) andmesubjekt on andnud nende andmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemiseks oma selges&otilde;nalise n&otilde;usoleku, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui liikmesriigi &otilde;igusaktides on s&auml;testatud, et andmesubjekti n&otilde;usolek ei saa kaotada l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud keeldu, v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> (b) processing is necessary for the purposes of carrying out the obligations and specific rights of the controller in the field of employment law in so far as it is authorized by national law providing for adequate safeguards; or </inglise>
<eesti> b) t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine on vajalik seoses vastutava t&ouml;&ouml;tleja kohustuste ja eri&otilde;igustega t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;iguse valdkonnas, kuiv&otilde;rd see on lubatud siseriikliku &otilde;igusega, milles on s&auml;testatud piisavad tagatised, v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> (c) processing is necessary to protect the vital interests of the data subject or of another person where the data subject is physically or legally incapable of giving his consent; or </inglise>
<eesti> c) t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine on vajalik selleks, et kaitsta andmesubjekti v&otilde;i m&otilde;ne teise isiku elulisi huve, kui andmesubjekt on f&uuml;&uuml;siliselt v&otilde;i &otilde;iguslikult v&otilde;imetu oma n&otilde;usolekut andma, v&otilde;i </eesti>
