<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> By way of derogation from Article 25 and save where otherwise provided by domestic law governing particular cases, Member States shall provide that a transfer or a set of transfers of personal data to a third country which does not ensure an adequate level of protection within the meaning of Article 25 (2) may take place on condition that: </inglise>
<eesti> Erandina artiklist 25, ja kui konkreetsete juhtude suhtes ei ole siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktidega ette n&auml;htud teisiti, s&auml;testavad liikmesriigid, et isikuandmete edastamine v&otilde;i edastamiste kogum kolmandasse riiki, mis ei taga piisavat kaitset artikli 25 l&otilde;ike 2 t&auml;henduses, v&otilde;ib toimuda tingimusel, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the data subject has given his consent unambiguously to the proposed transfer; or </inglise>
