<inglise> 6. </inglise>
<eesti> 6. </eesti>
<inglise> Each supervisory authority is competent, whatever the national law applicable to the processing in question, to exercise, on the territory of its own Member State, the powers conferred on it in accordance with paragraph 3. </inglise>
